   UNITED STATES BANKRUPTCY COURT FOR THE DISTRICT OF RHODE ISLAND - - - -
   - - - - - - - - - - - - - -x In re: : Amendments to Local Rules :
   EMERGENCY BANKRUPTCY ORDER Debtor No. 01-001 - - - - - - - - - - - - -
   - - - - -x EMERGENCY ORDER ABROGATING R.I. LBR 5001-2(B) AND
   AUTHORIZING THE CLERK TO REMOVE THE NIGHT DEPOSIT BOX Due to recent
   national events and in order to assist in assuring the safety of the
   employees and the public at the United States Bankruptcy Court for the
   District of Rhode Island, the Court will no longer accept any filings
   via the night deposit box. Until further order, R.I. LBR 5001-2(b)
   concerning use of the Night Deposit Box is hereby ABROGATED and the
   Clerk of the Bankruptcy Court is authorized to remove the night deposit
   box from its current location in front of the Courthouse. This
   Emergency Order shall take effect immediately, and shall apply to all
   cases filed on or after this date and to all cases pending in this
   Court as of this date. Enter: Order: /s/ Arthur N. Votolato /s/ Susan
   M. Thurston U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Clerk of Court Dated: September 14,
   2001
